<subSubSection pageId="30" pageNumber="139" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="30.[189,310,753,779]" box="[189,310,753,779]" pageId="30" pageNumber="139">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,310,753,779]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="30" pageNumber="139" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,310,753,779]" pageId="30" pageNumber="139">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="30.[189,1398,800,862]" pageId="30" pageNumber="139">Outer paleae lanceolate, compressed with sharp tips, elongated and slender. Inner paleae cylindrical, smooth, with blunt tip. Two to four tentacular filaments per lobe.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="30" pageNumber="139" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="30.[189,324,901,927]" box="[189,324,901,927]" pageId="30" pageNumber="139">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,324,901,927]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="30" pageNumber="139" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,324,901,927]" pageId="30" pageNumber="139">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="30.[188,1399,947,1009]" pageId="30" pageNumber="139">
This species is named in memory of my grandfather 
<collectingCountry box="[802,867,947,973]" name="Israel" pageId="30" pageNumber="139">Israel</collectingCountry>
López, an exemplary man. The species name is a noun in the genitive case (
<bibRefCitation author="ICZN &amp; International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature" box="[542,681,983,1009]" pageId="30" pageNumber="139" refId="ref15146" refString="ICZN (International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature). 1999. International Code of Zoological Nomenclature, 4 th Ed. International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature, The Natural History Museum, London. Available from https: // www. iczn. org / the-code / the-code-online / [accessed 31 Jan. 2022]." type="url" year="1999">ICZN 1999</bibRefCitation>
, Art. 31.1.2).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
