<subSubSection lastPageId="33" lastPageNumber="142" pageId="30" pageNumber="139" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="30.[189,334,1331,1357]" box="[189,334,1331,1357]" pageId="30" pageNumber="139">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,334,1331,1357]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="30" pageNumber="139" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,334,1331,1357]" pageId="30" pageNumber="139">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="30.[186,1399,1396,1458]" pageId="30" pageNumber="139">
<collectionCode box="[189,254,1397,1423]" pageId="30" pageNumber="139">BODY</collectionCode>
. 
<typeStatus box="[266,375,1396,1422]" pageId="30" pageNumber="139">Holotype</typeStatus>
complete (UMML-22.1195), very damaged, 
<quantity box="[892,972,1397,1423]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="30" pageNumber="139" unit="mm" value="40.0">40 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity box="[1040,1127,1396,1423]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="30" pageNumber="139" unit="mm" value="0.5">0.5 mm</quantity>
wide, four parathoracic segments, five abdominal segments (
<figureCitation box="[618,764,1432,1458]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="31.[189,232,1758,1784]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,265,1704]" captionTargetId="figure-11@31.[189,1398,265,1704]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="Fig. 18. Tetreres israeli sp. nov., holotype (UMML-22.1195). A. Complete specimen, dorsal view. B. Anterior region, dorsal view. C. Anterior region, lateral right view. D. Anterior region, ventral view. E. Paratype (UMML-22.1196). F. Operculum of the paratype. Abbreviations: ip = inner paleae; nh = nuchal hooks; op = outer paleae. Numbers indicate the tentacular filaments. Scale bars: A, C–E = 2 mm; B = 1 mm; F = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6885312" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6885312/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="139">Fig. 18A–D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="30.[188,1400,1497,1840]" pageId="30" pageNumber="139">
OPERCULUM. Opercular disc oblique. Opercular crown with almost all opercular paleae broken (
<figureCitation captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="31.[189,232,1758,1784]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,265,1704]" captionTargetId="figure-11@31.[189,1398,265,1704]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="Fig. 18. Tetreres israeli sp. nov., holotype (UMML-22.1195). A. Complete specimen, dorsal view. B. Anterior region, dorsal view. C. Anterior region, lateral right view. D. Anterior region, ventral view. E. Paratype (UMML-22.1196). F. Operculum of the paratype. Abbreviations: ip = inner paleae; nh = nuchal hooks; op = outer paleae. Numbers indicate the tentacular filaments. Scale bars: A, C–E = 2 mm; B = 1 mm; F = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6885312" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6885312/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="139">Fig. 18B– C</figureCitation>
). Outer paleae arranged in semicircles, seven paleae on left lobe, 18 on right (
<figureCitation box="[1171,1313,1532,1558]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="31.[189,232,1758,1784]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,265,1704]" captionTargetId="figure-11@31.[189,1398,265,1704]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="Fig. 18. Tetreres israeli sp. nov., holotype (UMML-22.1195). A. Complete specimen, dorsal view. B. Anterior region, dorsal view. C. Anterior region, lateral right view. D. Anterior region, ventral view. E. Paratype (UMML-22.1196). F. Operculum of the paratype. Abbreviations: ip = inner paleae; nh = nuchal hooks; op = outer paleae. Numbers indicate the tentacular filaments. Scale bars: A, C–E = 2 mm; B = 1 mm; F = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6885312" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6885312/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="139">Fig. 18B–F</figureCitation>
). Inner paleae in short ventral line on each inner margin of opercular lobes, three paleae on left lobe, four on right (
<figureCitation box="[262,401,1603,1629]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="31.[189,232,1758,1784]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,265,1704]" captionTargetId="figure-11@31.[189,1398,265,1704]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="Fig. 18. Tetreres israeli sp. nov., holotype (UMML-22.1195). A. Complete specimen, dorsal view. B. Anterior region, dorsal view. C. Anterior region, lateral right view. D. Anterior region, ventral view. E. Paratype (UMML-22.1196). F. Operculum of the paratype. Abbreviations: ip = inner paleae; nh = nuchal hooks; op = outer paleae. Numbers indicate the tentacular filaments. Scale bars: A, C–E = 2 mm; B = 1 mm; F = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6885312" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6885312/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="139">Fig. 18B, F</figureCitation>
). Outer paleae amber, lanceolate, compressed, 
<quantity box="[953,1021,1603,1629]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="30" pageNumber="139" unit="mm" value="3.0">3 mm</quantity>
long. Blade six times as long as wide (
<figureCitation box="[262,406,1638,1664]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="32.[189,232,1884,1910]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,490,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-61@32.[189,1398,490,1842]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="Fig. 19. Tetreres israeli sp. nov., holotype (UMML-22.1195). A. Outer palea. B. Tip of outer palea. C. Inner palea. D. Tip of inner palea. E. Nuchal hook, ventral view. F. Nuchal hook, lateral view. G. Abdominal parapodium. H. Abdominal chaetae. Abbreviation = Li, limbation. Scale bars: A, E = 200 µm; B, D, G = 100 µm; C = 1 mm; F = 0.5 mm; H = 30 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6885314" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6885314/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="139">Fig. 19A–B</figureCitation>
). Tip sharp, elongate, slender (
<figureCitation box="[763,870,1638,1664]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="32.[189,232,1884,1910]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,490,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-61@32.[189,1398,490,1842]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="Fig. 19. Tetreres israeli sp. nov., holotype (UMML-22.1195). A. Outer palea. B. Tip of outer palea. C. Inner palea. D. Tip of inner palea. E. Nuchal hook, ventral view. F. Nuchal hook, lateral view. G. Abdominal parapodium. H. Abdominal chaetae. Abbreviation = Li, limbation. Scale bars: A, E = 200 µm; B, D, G = 100 µm; C = 1 mm; F = 0.5 mm; H = 30 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6885314" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6885314/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="139">Fig. 19B</figureCitation>
). Inner paleae amber, cylindrical, smooth, tip blunt (
<figureCitation box="[264,407,1673,1699]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="32.[189,232,1884,1910]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,490,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-61@32.[189,1398,490,1842]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="Fig. 19. Tetreres israeli sp. nov., holotype (UMML-22.1195). A. Outer palea. B. Tip of outer palea. C. Inner palea. D. Tip of inner palea. E. Nuchal hook, ventral view. F. Nuchal hook, lateral view. G. Abdominal parapodium. H. Abdominal chaetae. Abbreviation = Li, limbation. Scale bars: A, E = 200 µm; B, D, G = 100 µm; C = 1 mm; F = 0.5 mm; H = 30 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6885314" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6885314/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="139">Fig. 19C–D</figureCitation>
). Opercular stalk orange to pale yellow, almost three times as long as wide (
<figureCitation box="[1279,1384,1673,1699]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="31.[189,232,1758,1784]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,265,1704]" captionTargetId="figure-11@31.[189,1398,265,1704]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="Fig. 18. Tetreres israeli sp. nov., holotype (UMML-22.1195). A. Complete specimen, dorsal view. B. Anterior region, dorsal view. C. Anterior region, lateral right view. D. Anterior region, ventral view. E. Paratype (UMML-22.1196). F. Operculum of the paratype. Abbreviations: ip = inner paleae; nh = nuchal hooks; op = outer paleae. Numbers indicate the tentacular filaments. Scale bars: A, C–E = 2 mm; B = 1 mm; F = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6885312" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6885312/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="139">Fig. 18B</figureCitation>
). Opercular papillae not observed. One pair of nuchal hooks amber, long, robust, with short limbation, tip strongly curved (
<figureCitation box="[438,549,1743,1770]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="31.[189,232,1758,1784]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,265,1704]" captionTargetId="figure-11@31.[189,1398,265,1704]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="Fig. 18. Tetreres israeli sp. nov., holotype (UMML-22.1195). A. Complete specimen, dorsal view. B. Anterior region, dorsal view. C. Anterior region, lateral right view. D. Anterior region, ventral view. E. Paratype (UMML-22.1196). F. Operculum of the paratype. Abbreviations: ip = inner paleae; nh = nuchal hooks; op = outer paleae. Numbers indicate the tentacular filaments. Scale bars: A, C–E = 2 mm; B = 1 mm; F = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6885312" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6885312/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="139">Figs 18B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[565,616,1744,1770]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="32.[189,232,1884,1910]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,490,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-61@32.[189,1398,490,1842]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="Fig. 19. Tetreres israeli sp. nov., holotype (UMML-22.1195). A. Outer palea. B. Tip of outer palea. C. Inner palea. D. Tip of inner palea. E. Nuchal hook, ventral view. F. Nuchal hook, lateral view. G. Abdominal parapodium. H. Abdominal chaetae. Abbreviation = Li, limbation. Scale bars: A, E = 200 µm; B, D, G = 100 µm; C = 1 mm; F = 0.5 mm; H = 30 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6885314" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6885314/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="139">19E</figureCitation>
). In lateral view, nuchal hooks distally curved at angle of ~115° (
<figureCitation box="[198,304,1779,1805]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="32.[189,232,1884,1910]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,490,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-61@32.[189,1398,490,1842]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="Fig. 19. Tetreres israeli sp. nov., holotype (UMML-22.1195). A. Outer palea. B. Tip of outer palea. C. Inner palea. D. Tip of inner palea. E. Nuchal hook, ventral view. F. Nuchal hook, lateral view. G. Abdominal parapodium. H. Abdominal chaetae. Abbreviation = Li, limbation. Scale bars: A, E = 200 µm; B, D, G = 100 µm; C = 1 mm; F = 0.5 mm; H = 30 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6885314" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6885314/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="139">Fig. 19F</figureCitation>
). Palps and median organ not observed. Tentacular filaments damaged, simple, slender; two tentacles on left lobe, four on right (
<figureCitation box="[612,719,1814,1840]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="31.[189,232,1758,1784]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,265,1704]" captionTargetId="figure-11@31.[189,1398,265,1704]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="Fig. 18. Tetreres israeli sp. nov., holotype (UMML-22.1195). A. Complete specimen, dorsal view. B. Anterior region, dorsal view. C. Anterior region, lateral right view. D. Anterior region, ventral view. E. Paratype (UMML-22.1196). F. Operculum of the paratype. Abbreviations: ip = inner paleae; nh = nuchal hooks; op = outer paleae. Numbers indicate the tentacular filaments. Scale bars: A, C–E = 2 mm; B = 1 mm; F = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6885312" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6885312/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="139">Fig. 18C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="30.[189,1399,1879,1941]" pageId="30" pageNumber="139">THORAX. First thoracic segment without cirrus or chaetae. Second segment with two triangular-shaped lateral lobes and paired branchiae.</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6885312" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6885312" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6885312/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="140" startId="31.[189,232,1758,1784]" targetBox="[189,1398,265,1704]" targetPageId="31">
<paragraph blockId="31.[189,1399,1758,1925]" pageId="31" pageNumber="140">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,287,1758,1784]" pageId="31" pageNumber="140">Fig. 18.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Chávez-López, 2022" authorityName="Chávez-López" authorityYear="2022" box="[299,479,1758,1784]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sabellariidae" genus="Tetreres" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="31" pageNumber="140" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="israeli" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[299,479,1758,1784]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="140">Tetreres israeli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[491,589,1758,1784]" pageId="31" pageNumber="140" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, holotype (UMML-22.1195). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[955,976,1758,1784]" pageId="31" pageNumber="140">A</emphasis>
. Complete specimen, dorsal view. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,209,1793,1819]" pageId="31" pageNumber="140">B</emphasis>
. Anterior region, dorsal view. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[569,590,1793,1819]" pageId="31" pageNumber="140">C</emphasis>
. Anterior region, lateral right view. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1015,1036,1793,1819]" pageId="31" pageNumber="140">D</emphasis>
. Anterior region, ventral view. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,208,1828,1854]" pageId="31" pageNumber="140">E</emphasis>
. Paratype (UMML-22.1196). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[571,587,1828,1854]" pageId="31" pageNumber="140">F</emphasis>
. Operculum of the paratype. Abbreviations: ip = inner paleae; nh = nuchal hooks; op = outer paleae. Numbers indicate the tentacular filaments. Scale bars: A, C–E = 2 mm; B = 1 mm; F = 0.5 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="32.[189,1399,265,326]" pageId="32" pageNumber="141">PARATHORAX. With four segments, branchiae not seen. Notopodia with lanceolate and capillary chaetae. Neurochaetae capillary.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="32.[189,1399,366,427]" pageId="32" pageNumber="141">
ABDOMEN. Abdominal segments yellowish, not very well defined. Neuropodia small, with capillary chaetae, ornamented with irregular thecal laminar extensions (
<figureCitation box="[801,944,401,427]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="32.[189,232,1884,1910]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,490,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-61@32.[189,1398,490,1842]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="Fig. 19. Tetreres israeli sp. nov., holotype (UMML-22.1195). A. Outer palea. B. Tip of outer palea. C. Inner palea. D. Tip of inner palea. E. Nuchal hook, ventral view. F. Nuchal hook, lateral view. G. Abdominal parapodium. H. Abdominal chaetae. Abbreviation = Li, limbation. Scale bars: A, E = 200 µm; B, D, G = 100 µm; C = 1 mm; F = 0.5 mm; H = 30 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6885314" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6885314/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="141">Fig. 19G–H</figureCitation>
). Notopodia robust, uncini not seen.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6885314" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6885314" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6885314/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="141" startId="32.[189,232,1884,1910]" targetBox="[189,1398,490,1842]" targetPageId="32">
