<subSubSection pageId="33" pageNumber="142" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="33.[189,303,377,403]" box="[189,303,377,403]" pageId="33" pageNumber="142">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,303,377,403]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="33" pageNumber="142" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,303,377,403]" pageId="33" pageNumber="142">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="33.[188,1399,423,555]" pageId="33" pageNumber="142">
In the Caribbean Sea and the Gulf of 
<collectingRegion box="[618,711,423,449]" country="Mexico" name="Mexico" pageId="33" pageNumber="142">Mexico</collectingRegion>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Treadwell, 1901)" baseAuthorityName="Treadwell" baseAuthorityYear="1901" box="[720,1125,423,449]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sabellariidae" genus="Tetreres" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="33" pageNumber="142" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="varians">
<emphasis box="[720,908,424,449]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="142">Tetreres varians</emphasis>
(Treadwell, 1901)
</taxonomicName>
was the only species of the genus recorded. 
<taxonomicName authority="Chávez-López, 2022" authorityName="Chávez-López" authorityYear="2022" box="[425,600,458,484]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sabellariidae" genus="Tetreres" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="33" pageNumber="142" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="israeli" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[425,600,458,484]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="142">Tetreres israeli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[608,698,459,485]" pageId="33" pageNumber="142" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Treadwell" baseAuthorityYear="1901" box="[755,871,459,484]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sabellariidae" genus="Tetreres" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="33" pageNumber="142" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="varians">
<emphasis box="[755,871,459,484]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="142">T. varians</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differ mainly in the morphology of the outer blades, being lanceolate in 
<taxonomicName authority="Chávez-López, 2022" authorityName="Chávez-López" authorityYear="2022" box="[517,624,493,519]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sabellariidae" genus="Tetreres" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="33" pageNumber="142" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="israeli" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[517,624,493,519]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="142">T. israeli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[633,726,494,520]" pageId="33" pageNumber="142" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(
<figureCitation box="[744,888,493,520]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="32.[189,232,1884,1910]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,490,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-61@32.[189,1398,490,1842]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="Fig. 19. Tetreres israeli sp. nov., holotype (UMML-22.1195). A. Outer palea. B. Tip of outer palea. C. Inner palea. D. Tip of inner palea. E. Nuchal hook, ventral view. F. Nuchal hook, lateral view. G. Abdominal parapodium. H. Abdominal chaetae. Abbreviation = Li, limbation. Scale bars: A, E = 200 µm; B, D, G = 100 µm; C = 1 mm; F = 0.5 mm; H = 30 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6885314" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6885314/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="142">Fig. 19A–B</figureCitation>
) and oblong in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Treadwell" baseAuthorityYear="1901" box="[1082,1201,494,519]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sabellariidae" genus="Tetreres" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="33" pageNumber="142" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="varians">
<emphasis box="[1082,1201,494,519]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="142">T. varians</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Augener H." box="[1219,1395,493,520]" pageId="33" pageNumber="142" pagination="91 - 196" refId="ref14524" refString="Augener H. 1906. Westindische Polychaeten. In: Reports on the results of dredging, under the supervision of Alexander Agassiz, in the Gulf of Mexico and the Caribbean Sea, and on the East Coast of the United States, 1877 - 1880, by the U. S. Coast Survey Steamer &quot; Blake &quot;. Bulletin of the Museum of Comparative Zoology 43 (4): 91 - 196. Available from https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 30295058 [accessed 31 Jan. 2022]." type="journal article" year="1906">Augener 1906</bibRefCitation>
: pl. 7, fig. 131; 
<bibRefCitation author="Kirtley D. W." box="[361,514,529,555]" pageId="33" pageNumber="142" refId="ref15203" refString="Kirtley D. W. 1994. A Review and Taxonomic Revision of the Family Sabellariidae Johnston, 1865 (Annelida: Polychaeta). Sabecon Press Science Series, Stuart, Florida." type="book" year="1994">Kirtley 1994</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 12.10.3a, d–f).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="33.[188,1398,594,691]" pageId="33" pageNumber="142">
The morphology of the paleae of 
<taxonomicName authority="Chávez-López, 2022" authorityName="Chávez-López" authorityYear="2022" box="[574,676,594,620]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sabellariidae" genus="Tetreres" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="33" pageNumber="142" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="israeli" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[574,676,594,620]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="142">T. israeli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[684,773,595,621]" pageId="33" pageNumber="142" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
resembles those of 
<taxonomicName authority="Kirtley, 1994" authorityName="Kirtley" authorityYear="1994" box="[1000,1261,594,620]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sabellariidae" genus="Tetreres" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="33" pageNumber="142" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="perryi">
<emphasis box="[1000,1100,595,620]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="142">T. perryi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Kirtley D. W." box="[1107,1261,594,620]" pageId="33" pageNumber="142" refId="ref15203" refString="Kirtley D. W. 1994. A Review and Taxonomic Revision of the Family Sabellariidae Johnston, 1865 (Annelida: Polychaeta). Sabecon Press Science Series, Stuart, Florida." type="book" year="1994">Kirtley, 1994</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(Northwest Atlantic). Both species have lanceolate outer paleae with elongate tips; however, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kirtley" authorityYear="1994" box="[1175,1279,630,655]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sabellariidae" genus="Tetreres" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="33" pageNumber="142" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="perryi">
<emphasis box="[1175,1279,630,655]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="142">T. perryi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has outer paleae with transverse irregular thecae, whereas 
<taxonomicName authority="Chávez-López, 2022" authorityName="Chávez-López" authorityYear="2022" box="[758,862,664,690]" class="Polychaeta" family="Sabellariidae" genus="Tetreres" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="33" pageNumber="142" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="israeli" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[758,862,664,690]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="142">T. israeli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[869,960,665,691]" pageId="33" pageNumber="142" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
has no transverse thecae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[189,1094,730,803]" pageId="33" pageNumber="142" type="distribution">
